<%- include('partials/head', { pageTitle: pageTitle || 'Editorial Team' }) %>
<%- include('partials/header', { categories }) %>
      <section class="info-page">
        <div class="container">
          <h1>Gaming Tech Ware Editorial Team</h1>
          <p class="lead">
            Our editorial desk blends experience across games journalism, analytics, and community management to ensure every story we publish is accurate, contextual, and useful for modern players.
          </p>
          <div class="info-grid">
            <section class="info-section">
              <h2>Collective Expertise</h2>
              <p>
                The team monitors console, PC, and mobile ecosystems day and night. We track live-service updates, esports investments, accessibility breakthroughs, and hardware roadmaps so you can grasp what matters without pausing your play session.
              </p>
              <ul>
                <li>Daily monitoring of studio announcements, regulatory filings, and investor calls.</li>
                <li>Hands-on familiarity with major platforms, competitive scenes, and creator communities.</li>
                <li>Experience translating technical engineering details into accessible context.</li>
              </ul>
            </section>
            <section class="info-section">
              <h2>Editorial Workflow</h2>
              <p>
                Every article goes through ideation, fact gathering, rewriting, and peer review. Automated tools surface leads, but final copy only ships after human editors verify numbers, add background, and align tone with our guidelines.
              </p>
              <ul>
                <li>Primary source validation and citation review.</li>
                <li>Headline and deck shaping to emphasize reader takeaways.</li>
                <li>Copy editing for clarity, neutrality, and consistency.</li>
              </ul>
            </section>
            <section class="info-section">
              <h2>Reader Commitments</h2>
              <p>
                We publish corrections promptly, flag updates when stories evolve, and avoid speculation unless clearly labelled. Feedback from readers informs future coverage priorities and helps us refine the format of daily summaries.
              </p>
              <p>
                If you spot a detail we should update, contact the team through our <a href="/contact">contact page</a>. We review every request within two business days.
              </p>
            </section>
            <section class="info-section">
              <h2>Coverage Principles</h2>
              <ul>
                <li>Focus on verifiable facts and reproducible data.</li>
                <li>Highlight impact on players, developers, and platform owners.</li>
                <li>Give indie creators and emerging regions visibility alongside major publishers.</li>
              </ul>
            </section>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>
